Add warnings when characters above 0xFF enter into Email::Simple

Whole Email::Simple works with bytes, not with Unicode strings. Therefore
add safe warnings about unexpected characters which cannot be represented
as bytes and which would cause serious problems.

For now only throw warnings, in future it can be fatal error.

changelog for headers/header_names fix
reformat some code from HEAD~

Fix iterating arrayref $headers when it is empty

Expression (0 .. int($#$headers / 2)) expand to list (0) when $headers is [].

It caused that both methods headers() and header_names() in list context
returned (undef) when there was no header defined. And it throw warning:
Use of uninitialized value $_ in lc at Email/Simple/Header.pm line 138.

Expression (0 .. @$headers / 2 - 1) expand to list () when $headers is [].

So it should fix it. Warnings were thrown also for header_raw() and
header_raw_set() methods.

only use arg to new as ref-to-str if it is a SCALAR ref

This check is not great.  We need better-defined semantics, to
clarify what kinds of objects will be treated what way.  Objects
that stringify should be stringified eagerly, probably.
